WEBVTT

00:00:08.840 --> 00:00:16.180 align:middle line:84%
>>Jesus came to experience the
reality of the spirit, a power,

00:00:16.180 --> 00:00:21.520 align:middle line:84%
a love that calls us to have a
particular concern for people

00:00:21.520 --> 00:00:25.110 align:middle line:84%
who have been pushed
aside by the powers

00:00:25.110 --> 00:00:31.290 align:middle line:84%
that be, for the
marginalized, the oppressed.

00:00:31.290 --> 00:00:36.790 align:middle line:84%
This, I think, is central to
the experience of holy mystery

00:00:36.790 --> 00:00:39.014 align:middle line:84%
as we experience
that holy mystery

00:00:39.014 --> 00:00:40.305 align:middle line:90%
through the teachings of Jesus.

00:00:40.305 --> 00:00:43.170 align:middle line:90%


00:00:43.170 --> 00:00:47.560 align:middle line:84%
>>We participate in
the mystery of Christ.

00:00:47.560 --> 00:00:50.660 align:middle line:84%
Paul said, you are
free in Christ.

00:00:50.660 --> 00:00:57.200 align:middle line:84%
Free of this old binding sin
of self-centeredness and pride.

00:00:57.200 --> 00:01:05.850 align:middle line:84%
Then you live in the vision
of love and kingdom of God,

00:01:05.850 --> 00:01:10.720 align:middle line:84%
which is feast of equals,
where justice is flowing.

00:01:10.720 --> 00:01:13.580 align:middle line:90%


00:01:13.580 --> 00:01:15.800 align:middle line:84%
>>When Jesus said,
"I am the truth,"

00:01:15.800 --> 00:01:18.200 align:middle line:84%
I understand that to mean
wherever there is truth,

00:01:18.200 --> 00:01:21.220 align:middle line:90%
there is Jesus.

00:01:21.220 --> 00:01:24.350 align:middle line:84%
So when we seek the truth,
we are seeking Jesus.

00:01:24.350 --> 00:01:28.260 align:middle line:84%
Or the Buddha would say,
we are seeking the Buddha.

00:01:28.260 --> 00:01:32.030 align:middle line:84%
Once a student asked a
teacher, who is the Buddha?

00:01:32.030 --> 00:01:35.180 align:middle line:84%
And the teacher
said, you are you.

00:01:35.180 --> 00:01:37.470 align:middle line:90%
Never mind about the Buddha.

00:01:37.470 --> 00:01:38.760 align:middle line:90%
Don't speak to someone else.

00:01:38.760 --> 00:01:40.680 align:middle line:84%
Don't imagine a Buddha
out there and start

00:01:40.680 --> 00:01:42.520 align:middle line:90%
speaking to that Buddha.

00:01:42.520 --> 00:01:44.025 align:middle line:90%
Just look deeply into yourself.

00:01:44.025 --> 00:01:59.540 align:middle line:90%


00:01:59.540 --> 00:02:05.520 align:middle line:84%
>>Buddha has enabled me to see
things about Jesus that I never

00:02:05.520 --> 00:02:07.870 align:middle line:84%
would have been able
to see without Buddha.

00:02:07.870 --> 00:02:13.290 align:middle line:90%


00:02:13.290 --> 00:02:15.200 align:middle line:84%
When I start finding
what I believe

00:02:15.200 --> 00:02:17.700 align:middle line:84%
is true in other
religions, of course

00:02:17.700 --> 00:02:20.040 align:middle line:90%
it doesn't remain in my head.

00:02:20.040 --> 00:02:22.750 align:middle line:10%
It touches my whole being,
my heart, my practice.

00:02:22.750 --> 00:02:28.660 align:middle line:10%
And I start adopting that
religion to some extent.

00:02:28.660 --> 00:02:33.610 align:middle line:10%
I am nurtured by two different
religious traditions,

00:02:33.610 --> 00:02:36.420 align:middle line:10%
my Christian
practice and beliefs

00:02:36.420 --> 00:02:39.800 align:middle line:10%
and my Buddhist
practice and beliefs.

00:02:39.800 --> 00:02:42.340 align:middle line:84%
And both of them--
now they're different.

00:02:42.340 --> 00:02:44.160 align:middle line:84%
That's what makes
it so interesting.

00:02:44.160 --> 00:02:47.960 align:middle line:84%
That's what makes it
exciting and fruitful.

00:02:47.960 --> 00:02:51.410 align:middle line:84%
My interest in and
Buddhism actually

00:02:51.410 --> 00:02:55.730 align:middle line:84%
goes way back to when
I was 13, 14 years old,

00:02:55.730 --> 00:02:59.580 align:middle line:84%
and I decided that I wanted
to become a missionary priest

00:02:59.580 --> 00:03:01.160 align:middle line:90%
in the Catholic church.

00:03:01.160 --> 00:03:02.660 align:middle line:90%
The beginning of a long process.

00:03:02.660 --> 00:03:05.330 align:middle line:84%
I went to the seminary
through all 14 years

00:03:05.330 --> 00:03:07.860 align:middle line:90%
and was ordained a priest.

00:03:07.860 --> 00:03:10.340 align:middle line:84%
But my primary motivation
in the beginning

00:03:10.340 --> 00:03:15.430 align:middle line:84%
was, since I loved all these
wonderful Buddhist people,

00:03:15.430 --> 00:03:17.460 align:middle line:84%
I felt I had to
convert them to Jesus.

00:03:17.460 --> 00:03:20.760 align:middle line:84%
Because otherwise
they're in big trouble.

00:03:20.760 --> 00:03:23.980 align:middle line:84%
Their eternal
salvation is at stake.

00:03:23.980 --> 00:03:30.760 align:middle line:84%
But as I then began to actually
study Buddhism-- and even more

00:03:30.760 --> 00:03:35.150 align:middle line:84%
so as I began to meet
Buddhists and enter

00:03:35.150 --> 00:03:40.480 align:middle line:84%
into dialogue with Buddhists--
my more academic interest

00:03:40.480 --> 00:03:45.570 align:middle line:84%
in Buddhism led to a
decision to start practicing.

00:03:45.570 --> 00:03:47.120 align:middle line:84%
Happily, I'm married
to a Buddhist.

00:03:47.120 --> 00:03:50.260 align:middle line:90%


00:03:50.260 --> 00:03:53.550 align:middle line:84%
Kathy and I do a lot of
talking, and exploring,

00:03:53.550 --> 00:03:55.140 align:middle line:90%
and sitting together.

00:03:55.140 --> 00:03:59.410 align:middle line:84%
And that has been
extremely enriching.

00:03:59.410 --> 00:04:09.070 align:middle line:84%
Buddhism helped me discover how
I might more deeply experience

00:04:09.070 --> 00:04:11.060 align:middle line:90%
the reality of God.

00:04:11.060 --> 00:04:15.550 align:middle line:84%
This was in the
Buddhist insistence

00:04:15.550 --> 00:04:20.380 align:middle line:84%
that truth-- they don't
use the word God--

00:04:20.380 --> 00:04:27.450 align:middle line:84%
but that truth, ultimate
reality, the way things are,

00:04:27.450 --> 00:04:33.530 align:middle line:84%
is to be found-- is to
be found within myself

00:04:33.530 --> 00:04:35.350 align:middle line:90%
and within this world.

00:04:35.350 --> 00:04:40.690 align:middle line:84%
In other words, what I call
God is not an entity out there

00:04:40.690 --> 00:04:43.270 align:middle line:90%
that has to step into my life.

00:04:43.270 --> 00:04:48.390 align:middle line:84%
Buddhism stresses, or
affirms, that truth

00:04:48.390 --> 00:04:52.370 align:middle line:84%
is that which we find
within this world.

00:04:52.370 --> 00:04:54.920 align:middle line:84%
It just answered so many
quest-- difficulties I had

00:04:54.920 --> 00:05:01.260 align:middle line:84%
with the-- what is oftentimes an
exaggerated Christian teaching,

00:05:01.260 --> 00:05:05.740 align:middle line:84%
and talking about God as if
God is this supreme entity

00:05:05.740 --> 00:05:11.760 align:middle line:84%
out there, this infinite
father being, this superperson.

00:05:11.760 --> 00:05:14.890 align:middle line:84%
That's why Buddha didn't
want to talk about God.

00:05:14.890 --> 00:05:16.660 align:middle line:84%
Because to talk
too much about God,

00:05:16.660 --> 00:05:19.570 align:middle line:84%
that distracted you-- you
looking out there, rather than

00:05:19.570 --> 00:05:20.870 align:middle line:90%
looking into yourself.

00:05:20.870 --> 00:05:23.280 align:middle line:84%
And so that was a
tremendous help.

00:05:23.280 --> 00:05:30.760 align:middle line:90%


00:05:30.760 --> 00:05:32.720 align:middle line:84%
>>When I was in Japan
as a young Jesuit,

00:05:32.720 --> 00:05:34.620 align:middle line:84%
I was teaching
English and baseball.

00:05:34.620 --> 00:05:39.700 align:middle line:84%
And we had a championship team
there with the high school

00:05:39.700 --> 00:05:44.500 align:middle line:84%
and the middle school boys
in Rokko High School in Kobe.

00:05:44.500 --> 00:05:47.960 align:middle line:10%
When I entered the Jesuits,
I was simply Catholic.

00:05:47.960 --> 00:05:52.110 align:middle line:84%
I never thought of being
interested in Buddhism.

00:05:52.110 --> 00:05:54.880 align:middle line:84%
The Second Vatican
Council changed everything

00:05:54.880 --> 00:05:56.820 align:middle line:90%
for Catholics.

00:05:56.820 --> 00:05:59.490 align:middle line:10%
The Jesuits,
following the counsel,

00:05:59.490 --> 00:06:04.900 align:middle line:10%
urged us not merely to tolerate
other religions, but to admire

00:06:04.900 --> 00:06:08.840 align:middle line:10%
them and to promote the
good that they have.

00:06:08.840 --> 00:06:10.770 align:middle line:10%
Because there's good
in every religion.

00:06:10.770 --> 00:06:15.080 align:middle line:10%
And our job was to find out what
was good, all that was good,

00:06:15.080 --> 00:06:17.840 align:middle line:10%
and promote it.

00:06:17.840 --> 00:06:20.919 align:middle line:84%
Promote it even as different
from our own understanding

00:06:20.919 --> 00:06:21.460 align:middle line:90%
of the truth.

00:06:21.460 --> 00:06:24.800 align:middle line:90%


00:06:24.800 --> 00:06:29.410 align:middle line:84%
And finally, more
than that, to practice

00:06:29.410 --> 00:06:32.050 align:middle line:84%
the truth of the other,
to walk in their shoes.

00:06:32.050 --> 00:06:34.240 align:middle line:84%
Because only if we walk
in their shoes could

00:06:34.240 --> 00:06:38.500 align:middle line:84%
we really understand them,
or can appreciate them.

00:06:38.500 --> 00:06:40.230 align:middle line:84%
I found out that
many Jesuits were

00:06:40.230 --> 00:06:44.190 align:middle line:84%
interested in Buddhism,
especially Zen Buddhism.

00:06:44.190 --> 00:06:47.735 align:middle line:84%
They introduced me to
Yamada Roshi of Kamakura,

00:06:47.735 --> 00:06:49.074 align:middle line:90%
who knew about us.

00:06:49.074 --> 00:06:50.740 align:middle line:84%
His son went to one
of our high schools,

00:06:50.740 --> 00:06:54.470 align:middle line:90%
and he was very open to us.

00:06:54.470 --> 00:06:57.110 align:middle line:84%
And he welcomed
me into his zendo,

00:06:57.110 --> 00:07:01.650 align:middle line:84%
which was another great gift,
because I really knew nothing.

00:07:01.650 --> 00:07:06.610 align:middle line:84%
But the personality of Yamada
Roshi touched me deeply.

00:07:06.610 --> 00:07:08.470 align:middle line:84%
And I can't explain
that either, why

00:07:08.470 --> 00:07:11.000 align:middle line:84%
this man-- just when he
walked into the zendo--

00:07:11.000 --> 00:07:13.390 align:middle line:90%
touched me so deeply.

00:07:13.390 --> 00:07:17.720 align:middle line:84%
I had the feeling
that this is it.

00:07:17.720 --> 00:07:19.870 align:middle line:84%
I read later Thomas
Merton said, when

00:07:19.870 --> 00:07:22.760 align:middle line:84%
he encountered Zen
Buddhism, he said,

00:07:22.760 --> 00:07:25.630 align:middle line:84%
I don't know what it
means yet, but this is it.

00:07:25.630 --> 00:07:28.130 align:middle line:84%
I guess it was
the reasonableness

00:07:28.130 --> 00:07:32.540 align:middle line:90%
of Zen, the sanity of it.

00:07:32.540 --> 00:07:37.680 align:middle line:84%
And the compassionate
lifestyle that it presented

00:07:37.680 --> 00:07:39.900 align:middle line:90%
was very appealing to me.

00:07:39.900 --> 00:07:43.670 align:middle line:84%
Appealing is-- is almost
a command in my spirit

00:07:43.670 --> 00:07:47.770 align:middle line:84%
that this should
be followed also.

00:07:47.770 --> 00:07:52.680 align:middle line:84%
I studied with Maezumi Roshi
for a semester of my sabbatical

00:07:52.680 --> 00:07:54.120 align:middle line:90%
in Los Angeles.

00:07:54.120 --> 00:07:57.990 align:middle line:84%
And then I met Glassman
Roshi, who at that time

00:07:57.990 --> 00:08:01.820 align:middle line:90%
was his heir apparent.

00:08:01.820 --> 00:08:06.150 align:middle line:84%
So Glassman Roshi then
became my teacher.

00:08:06.150 --> 00:08:09.210 align:middle line:84%
He was really wonderful
to me in every way.

00:08:09.210 --> 00:08:13.540 align:middle line:84%
When the time came, he
wanted me to be a teacher.

00:08:13.540 --> 00:08:15.590 align:middle line:84%
There were many Buddhists
who were upset by this,

00:08:15.590 --> 00:08:19.240 align:middle line:84%
because I was
Catholic and Jesuit.

00:08:19.240 --> 00:08:24.430 align:middle line:84%
Glassman said to them,
are we one, or are we not?

00:08:24.430 --> 00:08:27.400 align:middle line:84%
And they said, well,
he's not even a priest.

00:08:27.400 --> 00:08:28.559 align:middle line:90%
He's not a Zen priest.

00:08:28.559 --> 00:08:30.679 align:middle line:84%
And Glassman said,
he is a priest.

00:08:30.679 --> 00:08:33.049 align:middle line:90%
We have to ordain him again?

00:08:33.049 --> 00:08:34.630 align:middle line:90%
What is this about?

00:08:34.630 --> 00:08:38.650 align:middle line:84%
And so he faced down
some serious opposition.

00:08:38.650 --> 00:08:42.310 align:middle line:84%
So he probably understood
that the Zen practice does not

00:08:42.310 --> 00:08:44.570 align:middle line:90%
interfere with anyone's faith.

00:08:44.570 --> 00:08:46.320 align:middle line:90%
It's not about faith at all.

00:08:46.320 --> 00:08:50.730 align:middle line:84%
Zen is beyond yes
or no about God.

00:08:50.730 --> 00:08:56.380 align:middle line:84%
Zen is a skill, perhaps like
learning to play the piano.

00:08:56.380 --> 00:08:59.025 align:middle line:84%
And faith need
not enter into it.

00:08:59.025 --> 00:08:59.560 align:middle line:90%
It can.

00:08:59.560 --> 00:09:00.476 align:middle line:90%
It can enrich a faith.

00:09:00.476 --> 00:09:03.580 align:middle line:10%
If a person is deeply
practicing his own faith,

00:09:03.580 --> 00:09:05.490 align:middle line:10%
Zen can enrich it.

00:09:05.490 --> 00:09:07.220 align:middle line:10%
But for those who
have no faith, that's

00:09:07.220 --> 00:09:09.630 align:middle line:10%
perfectly all right too
from a Zen point of view.

00:09:09.630 --> 00:09:14.280 align:middle line:90%


00:09:14.280 --> 00:09:16.910 align:middle line:84%
We open the possibility of
people being themselves--

00:09:16.910 --> 00:09:20.730 align:middle line:84%
whatever that is--
without judging them.

00:09:20.730 --> 00:09:26.510 align:middle line:84%
This young monk went into the
mountains to find a teacher.

00:09:26.510 --> 00:09:30.380 align:middle line:84%
To find the teacher,
meaning to find life itself.

00:09:30.380 --> 00:09:32.380 align:middle line:84%
And deep in the mountains
he heard a voice.

00:09:32.380 --> 00:09:36.920 align:middle line:90%


00:09:36.920 --> 00:09:41.670 align:middle line:84%
The Japanese call this hearing
the voice of the cuckoo.

00:09:41.670 --> 00:09:44.430 align:middle line:84%
Something called him
deep in his own nature,

00:09:44.430 --> 00:09:48.540 align:middle line:90%
in his own mind and heart.

00:09:48.540 --> 00:09:54.610 align:middle line:84%
And the voice said, "All
things are impermanent."

00:09:54.610 --> 00:09:57.010 align:middle line:84%
And the young man was
deeply touched by this.

00:09:57.010 --> 00:09:59.970 align:middle line:84%
In other words, he heard
it, because he was silent,

00:09:59.970 --> 00:10:03.150 align:middle line:90%
because his search was thorough.

00:10:03.150 --> 00:10:07.669 align:middle line:84%
He heard the teaching, all
things are impermanent.

00:10:07.669 --> 00:10:15.080 align:middle line:90%


00:10:15.080 --> 00:10:18.470 align:middle line:84%
>>I was born and raised
in a third generation

00:10:18.470 --> 00:10:22.830 align:middle line:84%
Christian family in Korea,
Presbyterian family.

00:10:22.830 --> 00:10:27.720 align:middle line:84%
So I went to church every
morning and every Sunday.

00:10:27.720 --> 00:10:31.100 align:middle line:10%
But my encounter with
Buddhism actually

00:10:31.100 --> 00:10:34.900 align:middle line:10%
start with my personal struggle.

00:10:34.900 --> 00:10:38.190 align:middle line:10%
At the time, I was going
through my divorce.

00:10:38.190 --> 00:10:40.570 align:middle line:10%
And I didn't know
what to do about this.

00:10:40.570 --> 00:10:41.650 align:middle line:90%
I so much suffering.

00:10:41.650 --> 00:10:45.090 align:middle line:84%
I don't know whether
I do it, or I not.

00:10:45.090 --> 00:10:48.040 align:middle line:84%
I was teaching "Women and
Religion" in Cambridge

00:10:48.040 --> 00:10:50.010 align:middle line:90%
at the time.

00:10:50.010 --> 00:10:53.290 align:middle line:90%
Then one day I walk home.

00:10:53.290 --> 00:10:58.200 align:middle line:84%
I discovered this Korean temple
in the middle of Central Square

00:10:58.200 --> 00:11:00.500 align:middle line:90%
in Cambridge.

00:11:00.500 --> 00:11:08.060 align:middle line:84%
So I walk in, and they have
a meditation instruction.

00:11:08.060 --> 00:11:11.600 align:middle line:84%
So I sat and I learned
meditation instruction.

00:11:11.600 --> 00:11:15.960 align:middle line:84%
Because I need to do
something for my suffering.

00:11:15.960 --> 00:11:21.420 align:middle line:84%
Then I went up my very first
interview with the Zen master.

00:11:21.420 --> 00:11:25.090 align:middle line:84%
So he asked me,
why are you here?

00:11:25.090 --> 00:11:26.600 align:middle line:90%
So I say, oh, I'm suffering.

00:11:26.600 --> 00:11:29.500 align:middle line:84%
And I did all my
melodramatic stories

00:11:29.500 --> 00:11:33.480 align:middle line:90%
about I loved this man so much.

00:11:33.480 --> 00:11:36.000 align:middle line:84%
But he become a
religious fundamentalist.

00:11:36.000 --> 00:11:37.970 align:middle line:90%
What can I do?

00:11:37.970 --> 00:11:40.165 align:middle line:90%
And maybe I have to leave.

00:11:40.165 --> 00:11:47.420 align:middle line:84%
So I pour out all my suffering,
expecting his empathy.

00:11:47.420 --> 00:11:55.480 align:middle line:84%
Then Zen master looked at
me in a very quiet spirit,

00:11:55.480 --> 00:11:56.990 align:middle line:90%
and asked me, so?

00:11:56.990 --> 00:12:00.260 align:middle line:90%


00:12:00.260 --> 00:12:03.700 align:middle line:84%
I said, I told you all
this suffering story,

00:12:03.700 --> 00:12:06.450 align:middle line:84%
and you just-- your
question is so?

00:12:06.450 --> 00:12:08.690 align:middle line:90%
So I was kind of angry inside.

00:12:08.690 --> 00:12:11.810 align:middle line:84%
I felt this Zen
master doesn't know

00:12:11.810 --> 00:12:17.040 align:middle line:84%
Psychology 101 and
Pastoral Counseling 101.

00:12:17.040 --> 00:12:18.790 align:middle line:84%
He heard this
story of suffering.

00:12:18.790 --> 00:12:20.900 align:middle line:90%
He need to give some comfort.

00:12:20.900 --> 00:12:23.860 align:middle line:90%
But he said, so?

00:12:23.860 --> 00:12:27.340 align:middle line:90%
So I was kind of dumbfounded.

00:12:27.340 --> 00:12:32.800 align:middle line:84%
Then after a little bit
of silence he asked me,

00:12:32.800 --> 00:12:34.220 align:middle line:90%
it's very interesting.

00:12:34.220 --> 00:12:37.250 align:middle line:84%
The first noble
truth of Buddhism

00:12:37.250 --> 00:12:40.250 align:middle line:90%
is "life is suffering."

00:12:40.250 --> 00:12:43.340 align:middle line:90%
Everybody is suffering.

00:12:43.340 --> 00:12:45.810 align:middle line:84%
And you just think you
are the only one who

00:12:45.810 --> 00:12:48.990 align:middle line:90%
are suffering in this world.

00:12:48.990 --> 00:12:53.240 align:middle line:84%
So why do you think
you are so special?

00:12:53.240 --> 00:12:57.640 align:middle line:84%
The first question, first
koan, Zen Master Seung Sahn

00:12:57.640 --> 00:13:00.730 align:middle line:90%
asked me was, who are you?

00:13:00.730 --> 00:13:04.980 align:middle line:84%
Then he said, if you
don't know that answer,

00:13:04.980 --> 00:13:09.710 align:middle line:84%
go to the dharma room
and sit and meditate.

00:13:09.710 --> 00:13:13.520 align:middle line:84%
Just ask this
question, who am I?

00:13:13.520 --> 00:13:14.615 align:middle line:90%
Who am I?

00:13:14.615 --> 00:13:16.620 align:middle line:90%
And get the answer.

00:13:16.620 --> 00:13:20.850 align:middle line:84%
And if you get the answer,
come back to me and report.

00:13:20.850 --> 00:13:26.490 align:middle line:84%
And until that time, you just
sit down and ask who am I?

