00:27:57.110 --> 00:27:59.640 align:middle line:90%


00:27:59.640 --> 00:28:01.320 align:middle line:84%
>>Grace is not
something from outside.

00:28:01.320 --> 00:28:04.040 align:middle line:84%
Grace is the very
presence of God within us,

00:28:04.040 --> 00:28:09.180 align:middle line:90%
enlightening us, humanizing us.

00:28:09.180 --> 00:28:11.770 align:middle line:84%
The greater our humanity,
then the greater capacity

00:28:11.770 --> 00:28:16.120 align:middle line:84%
we have to receive God's grace
in Christian theological terms.

00:28:16.120 --> 00:28:20.010 align:middle line:84%
Thiard says the fire of heaven
has to come down on something.

00:28:20.010 --> 00:28:23.480 align:middle line:84%
We're expected to do our part
in developing our human nature,

00:28:23.480 --> 00:28:27.230 align:middle line:84%
even though that,
too, is a grace.

00:28:27.230 --> 00:28:30.620 align:middle line:84%
So every step forward we
take to develop our nature,

00:28:30.620 --> 00:28:36.040 align:middle line:84%
God's grace is there to meet
us, to enliven us, to enrich it.

00:28:36.040 --> 00:28:42.005 align:middle line:84%
To become one with yourself,
to see the breadth of the self,

00:28:42.005 --> 00:28:45.430 align:middle line:84%
or the light of the self,
or the beauty of the self,

00:28:45.430 --> 00:28:49.080 align:middle line:84%
is then to recognize the
breadth, and the beauty,

00:28:49.080 --> 00:28:50.770 align:middle line:90%
and the light of Christ.

00:28:50.770 --> 00:28:52.190 align:middle line:90%
Because we are not separate.

00:28:52.190 --> 00:28:55.110 align:middle line:84%
It is Christ growing within
us in all that we do.

00:28:55.110 --> 00:28:59.410 align:middle line:90%


00:28:59.410 --> 00:29:02.670 align:middle line:84%
We can think of Christ
in a relational sense,

00:29:02.670 --> 00:29:06.370 align:middle line:84%
that Christ is another
whom we love, or serve,

00:29:06.370 --> 00:29:08.200 align:middle line:90%
or something like that.

00:29:08.200 --> 00:29:13.150 align:middle line:84%
But it is also very Catholic to
see that Christ is not other.

00:29:13.150 --> 00:29:15.840 align:middle line:90%


00:29:15.840 --> 00:29:20.270 align:middle line:84%
I am not simply a
friend of Christ,

00:29:20.270 --> 00:29:21.545 align:middle line:90%
but I am Christ himself.

00:29:21.545 --> 00:29:24.080 align:middle line:90%


00:29:24.080 --> 00:29:25.810 align:middle line:84%
Do you not know,
as Saint Paul says,

00:29:25.810 --> 00:29:28.230 align:middle line:90%
you are the body of Christ?

00:29:28.230 --> 00:29:29.290 align:middle line:90%
You are Christ himself.

00:29:29.290 --> 00:29:33.560 align:middle line:90%
And the other is Christ himself.

00:29:33.560 --> 00:29:36.820 align:middle line:84%
It's that unity of
Christ with the world

00:29:36.820 --> 00:29:41.760 align:middle line:84%
and with each one of us that
is an intimacy of identity, not

00:29:41.760 --> 00:29:44.920 align:middle line:90%
just relationship, but identity.

00:29:44.920 --> 00:29:47.849 align:middle line:84%
So everyone we meet, as the
Irish prayer says, is Christ.

00:29:47.849 --> 00:29:58.330 align:middle line:90%


00:29:58.330 --> 00:30:02.970 align:middle line:84%
>>Saint Paul writes to
the Galatian community.

00:30:02.970 --> 00:30:07.330 align:middle line:84%
He says, it is no
longer I who live,

00:30:07.330 --> 00:30:12.030 align:middle line:84%
but Christ who lives
in me and as me.

00:30:12.030 --> 00:30:15.500 align:middle line:90%
Paul is saying, I'm not living.

00:30:15.500 --> 00:30:19.100 align:middle line:84%
It's Christ who's
living, however, in me.

00:30:19.100 --> 00:30:21.782 align:middle line:84%
Buddhism is helping
me to comprehend that.

00:30:21.782 --> 00:30:27.250 align:middle line:84%
That brings me to a different
understanding of Paul Knitter.

00:30:27.250 --> 00:30:31.552 align:middle line:90%


00:30:31.552 --> 00:30:35.530 align:middle line:84%
When you can really be
mindful of this present moment

00:30:35.530 --> 00:30:38.980 align:middle line:84%
and recognizing that
its depth, its mystery,

00:30:38.980 --> 00:30:41.730 align:middle line:84%
is deeper than any
thought you have,

00:30:41.730 --> 00:30:45.640 align:middle line:84%
any feeling that you have, it's
hard to find words for this.

00:30:45.640 --> 00:30:47.260 align:middle line:84%
That's when you
feel that you are

00:30:47.260 --> 00:30:52.600 align:middle line:84%
held, that you are sustained,
that what you really are

00:30:52.600 --> 00:30:56.930 align:middle line:84%
is deeper than what
you think you are,

00:30:56.930 --> 00:31:01.350 align:middle line:84%
or than anything
anybody says you are.

00:31:01.350 --> 00:31:02.080 align:middle line:90%
It's deeper.

00:31:02.080 --> 00:31:04.780 align:middle line:84%
And that reality is
the Christ spirit.

00:31:04.780 --> 00:31:07.100 align:middle line:84%
That reality is
our Buddha nature.

00:31:07.100 --> 00:31:08.530 align:middle line:90%
That's who I really am.

00:31:08.530 --> 00:31:14.790 align:middle line:84%
Buddhists say, if you can really
be mindful of this moment,

00:31:14.790 --> 00:31:18.290 align:middle line:84%
it will provide
all that you need.

00:31:18.290 --> 00:31:19.220 align:middle line:90%
That's the power.

00:31:19.220 --> 00:31:20.240 align:middle line:90%
That's the beauty.

00:31:20.240 --> 00:31:25.170 align:middle line:84%
Because when you are
mindful of your thinking,

00:31:25.170 --> 00:31:31.700 align:middle line:84%
and you don't let
your thinking define

00:31:31.700 --> 00:31:34.230 align:middle line:90%
what is real in this moment.

00:31:34.230 --> 00:31:39.000 align:middle line:84%
My thought that I am-- I'm
thinking that I'm afraid.

00:31:39.000 --> 00:31:40.950 align:middle line:84%
I'm thinking that
I'm inadequate.

00:31:40.950 --> 00:31:44.510 align:middle line:84%
I'm thinking that-- I
mean-- or I feel I'm angry.

00:31:44.510 --> 00:31:50.150 align:middle line:84%
When I'm aware of my anger, when
I'm aware of my fear, and I say

00:31:50.150 --> 00:31:52.890 align:middle line:90%
that's my feeling.

00:31:52.890 --> 00:31:58.420 align:middle line:84%
That's not what is
real in this moment.

00:31:58.420 --> 00:32:00.070 align:middle line:90%
What is really real?

00:32:00.070 --> 00:32:03.540 align:middle line:84%
The thoughts that I have and
the feelings that I have of

00:32:03.540 --> 00:32:09.690 align:middle line:84%
despondency, of inadequacy,
of meaninglessness.

00:32:09.690 --> 00:32:11.240 align:middle line:90%
Be aware of them.

00:32:11.240 --> 00:32:13.080 align:middle line:90%
Let them be.

00:32:13.080 --> 00:32:14.049 align:middle line:90%
Don't fight them.

00:32:14.049 --> 00:32:15.590 align:middle line:84%
Because so often in
the past, I'd go,

00:32:15.590 --> 00:32:17.275 align:middle line:84%
oh, I shouldn't be
feeling this way.

00:32:17.275 --> 00:32:19.690 align:middle line:84%
Well damn it, I
do feel this way.

00:32:19.690 --> 00:32:23.980 align:middle line:90%
This is who I-- Accept that.

00:32:23.980 --> 00:32:27.760 align:middle line:84%
There's a certain
kind of letting

00:32:27.760 --> 00:32:32.060 align:middle line:90%
go which includes acceptance.

00:32:32.060 --> 00:32:35.510 align:middle line:84%
You accept the fact of
what you're feeling.

00:32:35.510 --> 00:32:37.290 align:middle line:90%
And then you let it go.

00:32:37.290 --> 00:32:40.950 align:middle line:90%
But first you have to accept it.

00:32:40.950 --> 00:32:47.660 align:middle line:84%
There is something that can be
almost miraculous about that.

00:32:47.660 --> 00:32:51.060 align:middle line:90%


00:32:51.060 --> 00:32:54.430 align:middle line:84%
>>When we sit well, all
our sins, if you will,

00:32:54.430 --> 00:32:58.420 align:middle line:84%
or our limitations disappear
like frost or snow.

00:32:58.420 --> 00:33:00.110 align:middle line:90%
They just vanish.

00:33:00.110 --> 00:33:02.900 align:middle line:84%
Because this moment is the
only moment that truly exists.

00:33:02.900 --> 00:33:07.330 align:middle line:84%
The past is memory; the
future is speculation.

00:33:07.330 --> 00:33:08.330 align:middle line:90%
Sit right now.

00:33:08.330 --> 00:33:09.175 align:middle line:90%
Work right now.

00:33:09.175 --> 00:33:10.730 align:middle line:90%
Serve right now.

00:33:10.730 --> 00:33:13.340 align:middle line:90%
Do it well.

00:33:13.340 --> 00:33:16.310 align:middle line:84%
As we get older, we
realize our limitations.

00:33:16.310 --> 00:33:17.830 align:middle line:90%
They can almost crush us.

00:33:17.830 --> 00:33:23.740 align:middle line:84%
And we realize the difficulty
of change, even for the better.

00:33:23.740 --> 00:33:28.260 align:middle line:84%
But it is not good
Zen practice to become

00:33:28.260 --> 00:33:31.330 align:middle line:84%
obsessed with the idea
of growth, or change,

00:33:31.330 --> 00:33:33.330 align:middle line:90%
or enlightenment.

00:33:33.330 --> 00:33:38.370 align:middle line:90%
That can just make us sick.

00:33:38.370 --> 00:33:41.315 align:middle line:84%
We must accept ourselves
as we are in this moment.

00:33:41.315 --> 00:33:44.450 align:middle line:90%


00:33:44.450 --> 00:33:48.910 align:middle line:84%
Accept the light that we
have, even if we don't see it.

00:33:48.910 --> 00:33:51.307 align:middle line:84%
And be grateful for it
and grateful for the gifts

00:33:51.307 --> 00:33:56.640 align:middle line:90%
of others who can teach us.

00:33:56.640 --> 00:34:00.910 align:middle line:84%
Don't tie ourselves in a knot
trying to improve ourselves.

00:34:00.910 --> 00:34:03.154 align:middle line:84%
That just puts the
emphasis back on the self

00:34:03.154 --> 00:34:04.070 align:middle line:90%
instead of the moment.

00:34:04.070 --> 00:34:06.840 align:middle line:90%


00:34:06.840 --> 00:34:13.650 align:middle line:10%
For me, zazen is prayer, to come
into the presence of mystery

00:34:13.650 --> 00:34:18.530 align:middle line:10%
and sit with attention,
physical attention, too.

00:34:18.530 --> 00:34:22.420 align:middle line:84%
Physical attention in the
presence of ultimate truth.

00:34:22.420 --> 00:34:26.340 align:middle line:84%
To sit with reverence for
that truth and gratitude

00:34:26.340 --> 00:34:30.100 align:middle line:84%
for the experience
itself is prayer.

00:34:30.100 --> 00:34:33.909 align:middle line:84%
Attention, reverence,
gratitude need not be spoken.

00:34:33.909 --> 00:34:36.400 align:middle line:90%
We don't have to use the words.

00:34:36.400 --> 00:34:37.940 align:middle line:90%
What would I do with words?

00:34:37.940 --> 00:34:41.230 align:middle line:84%
Would I try to remind God
of something God forgot?

00:34:41.230 --> 00:34:44.960 align:middle line:84%
Would I beseech God to pay
attention to someone else,

00:34:44.960 --> 00:34:47.752 align:middle line:84%
as if God was not
paying attention?

00:34:47.752 --> 00:34:50.650 align:middle line:90%


00:34:50.650 --> 00:34:53.390 align:middle line:84%
>>Being fully in
the present moment

00:34:53.390 --> 00:35:00.180 align:middle line:84%
is when joyful situation
arise, you become joyful.

00:35:00.180 --> 00:35:05.220 align:middle line:84%
A very painful situation
arise, and you feel pain.

00:35:05.220 --> 00:35:08.950 align:middle line:84%
And something sad
appears, you are sad.

00:35:08.950 --> 00:35:12.350 align:middle line:84%
And something really
fantastic appears,

00:35:12.350 --> 00:35:16.290 align:middle line:90%
you are totally surprised.

00:35:16.290 --> 00:35:22.730 align:middle line:84%
So you are like a very
fresh child, in a way,

00:35:22.730 --> 00:35:26.130 align:middle line:84%
to see everything
for the first time.

00:35:26.130 --> 00:35:30.760 align:middle line:84%
It's like falling
in love with life,

00:35:30.760 --> 00:35:35.330 align:middle line:84%
as if every moment
is your first love.

00:35:35.330 --> 00:35:38.900 align:middle line:90%
So that is a present moment.

00:35:38.900 --> 00:35:42.630 align:middle line:84%
But I didn't know it
when I was younger,

00:35:42.630 --> 00:35:48.050 align:middle line:84%
because I have big
dreams and big ambitions.

00:35:48.050 --> 00:35:51.480 align:middle line:90%
And I wanted so much in life.

00:35:51.480 --> 00:35:52.430 align:middle line:90%
And I want this.

00:35:52.430 --> 00:35:54.190 align:middle line:90%
I want that.

00:35:54.190 --> 00:36:00.200 align:middle line:84%
And then so much want always
brings so much suffering.

00:36:00.200 --> 00:36:03.280 align:middle line:84%
So there are moment
in my life I had

00:36:03.280 --> 00:36:05.670 align:middle line:90%
a really dark night of soul.

00:36:05.670 --> 00:36:08.700 align:middle line:90%
I walked into the valley.

00:36:08.700 --> 00:36:14.310 align:middle line:84%
And sometimes I got so
depressed it is unbearable.

00:36:14.310 --> 00:36:19.130 align:middle line:84%
And that moment, I learned
how to be in present moment

00:36:19.130 --> 00:36:24.620 align:middle line:84%
from my psychotherapist and
from my great Buddhist teachers.

00:36:24.620 --> 00:36:26.330 align:middle line:90%
Present moment.

00:36:26.330 --> 00:36:29.840 align:middle line:90%
That's all we have.

00:36:29.840 --> 00:36:36.440 align:middle line:84%
It's this very moment,
only here, and only now.

00:36:36.440 --> 00:36:42.800 align:middle line:84%
And that is what life is
presenting to us every moment.

00:36:42.800 --> 00:36:47.910 align:middle line:84%
And we miss this,
we miss entire life.

00:36:47.910 --> 00:36:51.410 align:middle line:90%
I wish I got it 30 years ago.

00:36:51.410 --> 00:36:54.240 align:middle line:90%
But that is all we have.

00:36:54.240 --> 00:36:58.830 align:middle line:84%
But most of us are really
most of the time regretting

00:36:58.830 --> 00:37:03.141 align:middle line:84%
about the past and
worrying about future.

00:37:03.141 --> 00:37:10.540 align:middle line:84%
But when we really know how
to be at the present moment,

00:37:10.540 --> 00:37:15.110 align:middle line:84%
then even big
suffering is bearable.

00:37:15.110 --> 00:37:24.430 align:middle line:84%
So present moment in my very
difficult time of life--

00:37:24.430 --> 00:37:26.050 align:middle line:90%
it pulled me through.

00:37:26.050 --> 00:37:34.730 align:middle line:84%
It carried me like a great wind,
a great love, or a very loving

00:37:34.730 --> 00:37:44.690 align:middle line:84%
mother take me just this moment,
next moment, next moment.

00:37:44.690 --> 00:37:45.810 align:middle line:90%
Then you will be fine.

00:37:45.810 --> 00:37:48.880 align:middle line:90%


00:37:48.880 --> 00:37:53.040 align:middle line:84%
