00:41:24.010 --> 00:41:26.890 align:middle line:84%
>>That is why interfaith
dialogue is so important.

00:41:26.890 --> 00:41:30.430 align:middle line:84%
It's not always that they teach
us something entirely new,

00:41:30.430 --> 00:41:33.150 align:middle line:84%
but they might frame it
in a way that energizes us

00:41:33.150 --> 00:41:36.530 align:middle line:84%
in a way our own vocabulary
did not energize us.

00:41:36.530 --> 00:41:39.940 align:middle line:84%
Sometimes we say the same things
over and over in the liturgy

00:41:39.940 --> 00:41:43.250 align:middle line:84%
and so on, and we lose
the urgency of words

00:41:43.250 --> 00:41:45.440 align:middle line:90%
or the depth of words.

00:41:45.440 --> 00:41:47.340 align:middle line:84%
When it comes in a
different vocabulary,

00:41:47.340 --> 00:41:50.700 align:middle line:84%
from a different framework,
sometimes you say,

00:41:50.700 --> 00:41:52.810 align:middle line:90%
why wasn't I told this before?

00:41:52.810 --> 00:41:57.590 align:middle line:84%
Well of course, you were told
before, but you see it anew.

00:41:57.590 --> 00:42:00.700 align:middle line:90%
>>Christianity is my father.

00:42:00.700 --> 00:42:03.450 align:middle line:90%
Buddhism is like my mother.

00:42:03.450 --> 00:42:08.010 align:middle line:84%
They came together, and I
become a Buddhist Christian.

00:42:08.010 --> 00:42:13.960 align:middle line:84%
And I hope this new
generation of young people

00:42:13.960 --> 00:42:17.710 align:middle line:84%
and next generation
of the children

00:42:17.710 --> 00:42:23.190 align:middle line:84%
can get more benefit from
the learning from world

00:42:23.190 --> 00:42:29.060 align:middle line:84%
great tradition, and
world great religions,

00:42:29.060 --> 00:42:32.340 align:middle line:90%
and the wisdom in compassion.

00:42:32.340 --> 00:42:38.840 align:middle line:84%
So rather than excluding
some religions in order

00:42:38.840 --> 00:42:41.830 align:middle line:84%
to be faithful to
your religion, you

00:42:41.830 --> 00:42:44.580 align:middle line:84%
can be fully faithful
to your religion,

00:42:44.580 --> 00:42:50.450 align:middle line:84%
but also open wide
to other wisdom.

00:42:50.450 --> 00:42:54.390 align:middle line:84%
Thich Nhat Hanh said
these beautiful things

00:42:54.390 --> 00:42:57.990 align:middle line:84%
in Christian root and
Buddhist root get together,

00:42:57.990 --> 00:43:01.310 align:middle line:90%
and you have a grafting of tree.

00:43:01.310 --> 00:43:05.280 align:middle line:84%
And it become a bigger
tree and more beautiful,

00:43:05.280 --> 00:43:07.460 align:middle line:90%
flourishing tree.

00:43:07.460 --> 00:43:11.460 align:middle line:84%
So under that
beautiful green shadow,

00:43:11.460 --> 00:43:15.350 align:middle line:84%
more people can
find peace and rest.

